<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued March 30 at 4:22AM EDT until March 30 at 12:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON EDT
TODAY...
* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations of
less than a half inch and ice accumulations of up to one tenth
of an inch. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.
* WHERE...Huron, Lapeer, Sanilac, Tuscola, Macomb and St. Clair
Counties.
* WHEN...Until noon EDT today.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Freezing rain is likely to continue through
this morning. Sleet and snow may mix in at times early this
morning as well. Temperatures are expected to gradually rise
above freezing by noon, supporting just rain showers or drizzle
this afternoon.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
